definition:
&%NinoRegion is a class of predefined regions located
in the tropical &%PacificOcean where their &%seaSurfaceTemperature are moniotred to track the onset at
various phases of the &%ElNinoSouthernOscillation. The numbers of the Niño 1,2,3, and 4 regions 
correspond with the labels assigned to ship tracks that crossed these regions.  Data from these 
tracks enabled the historic records of El Niño to be carried back in time to 1949. [US National 
Science Foundation, National Center For Atomspheric Research]
